    <stitle>AFC 00908 - Addition of a Relay to the Electrical Circuit in IC Bus Models Built Between March 20, 2000 and
        September 7, 2000 with Hydraulic Brakes
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc00908">
        <afcnum>00908</afcnum>
        <afcdate>February, 2001</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subject>Addition of a Relay to the Electrical Circuit in IC Bus Models Built Between March 20, 2000 and
            September 7, 2000 with Hydraulic Brakes
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>IC Bus
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/20/2000</startdate>
                        <enddate>09/07/2000</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The brake warning light and buzzer in IC Bus Models built between March 20, 2000 and September 7,
                    2000 may activate and give a false warning of a hydraulic brake system malfunction. This false
                    warning usually occurs when the vehicle is stopped for an extended period of time with light brake
                    pedal pressure, for an example at a stop sign or stop light. Performing this service procedure will
                    prevent the false warning from occurring.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
